description:
### What happens?

I observed this when reviewing https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb-python/issues/107:

#### Problem
Repeated copies to parquet get slower. 

#### Environments:
I tested this first in duckdb-python 1.4.1, then reproduced in duckdb-cli. 

#### Windows Store (?!?!)
What's *very very* confusing is - this *does not* reproduce when running in Windows Store's python. This suggests that the culprit is related to something that is bypassed when running in Windows MSIX isolation. 

See https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb-python/issues/107 for a discussion. 

#### Test output
duckdb-cli output of 40 runs (abbreviated)
