This reproduces on duckdb-python.


### Edit 1: Commentary
The fact that real time increases, with constant user & sys time... and the fact that it doesn't reproduce in MSIX... suggests it might be the Windows filter drivers / caching layers causing the delay.

And, even if the cause is external to the duckdb code, this does suggest possibly ways to improve the behavior... whether by reducing flushing, larger buffers, or even releasing the duckdb-cli as an MSIX. 

